# restic-backup.env — copy to /etc/restic/env, fill in, then: sudo chmod 600 /etc/restic/env
# Sourced (set -a) by restic-backup.sh / restore-test.sh / restic-latest-age.
# Plain KEY=VALUE lines — no `export` needed. Secrets live HERE, never in git.
#
# Backblaze B2 docs: https://www.backblaze.com/docs/cloud-storage-integrate-restic-with-backblaze-b2
# NOTE: A Synology NAS does NOT qualify for B2's flat $99 "Personal/Computer Backup" plan.
#       These Linux hosts use per-TB B2 Cloud Storage ($6.95/TB-month, effective May 1 2026) via this restic repo.

# --- Option A: native B2 backend (what mini + rig use) ----------------------------
# Repo format: b2:<bucket-name>:<path-prefix>  (prefix = short hostname)
RESTIC_REPOSITORY="b2:bucket-restic:CHANGEME-hostname"
# IMMUTABILITY (sec-03, 2026-07-14): RECOVERABLE immutability via a restricted key +
# B2 versioning + a lifecycle rule. Use the RESTRICTED "restic-append-only" B2 key here
# (vault: backblaze_b2.restic_append_only_key_id / _key) — listBuckets/listFiles/readFiles/
# writeFiles, but NO deleteFiles/bypassGovernance. restic's native B2 backend "deletes" by
# HIDING (writeFiles), so backup/forget/prune all work, but this key can NEVER hard-delete a
# file version. B2 keeps the hidden prior versions, and the bucket lifecycle rule
# `daysFromHidingToDeleting:30` retains them 30 days. Net: a compromised host can hide/
# overwrite but CANNOT destroy history — any hide/overwrite is recoverable for 30d, and hard
# deletion needs deleteFiles+bypassGovernance which only the vaulted MASTER key has. NEVER
# put the master key here.
# NOTE: we deliberately do NOT use a B2 Object-Lock *default retention* — it locks restic's
# own lock files, which restic then can't remove (no bypass headers), so every op slow-
# retries and `restic snapshots` ballooned to ~100s. Object Lock stays *enabled* on the
# bucket (permanent) but retention is `none`. Hyper Backup bucket: unchanged.
B2_ACCOUNT_ID="your_b2_keyID          # the restricted restic-append-only key ID"
B2_ACCOUNT_KEY="your_b2_applicationKey  # the restricted key"

# --- Option B: S3-compatible backend (use INSTEAD of Option A, not both) ---------
# Find your endpoint on the B2 Buckets page (e.g. s3.us-west-002.backblazeb2.com).
# RESTIC_REPOSITORY="s3:s3.us-west-002.backblazeb2.com/my-homelab-restic"
# AWS_ACCESS_KEY_ID="your_b2_keyID"
# AWS_SECRET_ACCESS_KEY="your_b2_applicationKey"

# --- Repository encryption password ----------------------------------------------
# Either inline (this file is root 0600) or via RESTIC_PASSWORD_FILE.
# >>> BACK THIS PASSWORD UP in your password manager AND on paper. Lose it = data unrecoverable. <<<
RESTIC_PASSWORD="CHANGEME"
# RESTIC_PASSWORD_FILE="/etc/restic/password"

# --- What to back up ---------------------------------------------------------------
# mini: BACKUP_PATHS="/opt/stacks /etc /home/btabaska/.ssh /home/btabaska/.config /home/btabaska/.docker /home/btabaska/.bashrc"
# rig:  BACKUP_PATHS="/etc /home/btabaska /opt/stacks/palworld/game/Pal/Saved /opt/stacks/palworld/game/backups /opt/stacks/amp/config/.ampdata/instances /var/lib/docker/volumes/docker_litellm_pgdata /var/lib/docker/volumes/docker_open_webui_data"
#   NB rig does NOT back up all of /opt — only game-world *state* under it, plus the
#   litellm-db (Postgres) and open-webui docker volumes (added fix-20, 2026-07-16 —
#   the RO-disk incident showed this data had no backup at all). steamcmd server
#   binaries and re-downloadable AMP/Minecraft jars/libraries are excluded (huge);
#   see excludes-rig.txt on the host.
BACKUP_PATHS="/etc"
# Host-specific exclude patterns (deploy scripts/backup/excludes-<host>.txt here):
RESTIC_EXCLUDE_FILE="/etc/restic/excludes.txt"
# Optional consistent-dump hook run before the snapshot (mini only):
# PRE_BACKUP_SCRIPT="/opt/scripts/pre-backup-db-dumps.sh"

# --- Retention (forget daily; --prune added on PRUNE_WEEKDAY, 1=Mon..7=Sun) --------
KEEP_DAILY=7
KEEP_WEEKLY=4
KEEP_MONTHLY=6
KEEP_YEARLY=0
PRUNE_WEEKDAY=7

# --- Healthchecks dead-man success ping (fix-42) -----------------------------------
# Curled by the restic-backup.service.d/healthchecks.conf drop-in after every
# SUCCESSFUL backup (vault: healthchecks.restic_mini_ping_url / restic_rig_ping_url).
# Leave unset to disable. The drop-in sources this file with sh — NEVER point a
# systemd EnvironmentFile= at it: systemd logs rejected lines (e.g. `export`-style)
# VERBATIM to the journal, which leaked these secrets on 2026-07-19.
# RESTIC_HC_URL="http://192.168.10.2:8001/ping/CHANGEME"

# --- ntfy failure alerts (rig only — mini's ntfy-notify.sh reads /etc/verification/env)
# NTFY_URL="http://macmini:8080/backups"
# NTFY_TOKEN="tk_..."
